By ET Now | 9 May, 2016, 12.00PM IST
CLSA maintains high conviction buy on Reliance Industries post March quarter results and has also raised its 12-month target price to Rs 1,350 from Rs 1,275 earlier.The global investment bank assumes commercial launch of Reliance Jio by Sep or Oct 2016.
It has model in 25m and 70m subscribers by the end of FY17 and FY18 for Jio, said the investment bank.
CLSA estimates Jio's EBITDA/FCF/PBT break-even in FY18/19/20.
The bank has factored in initial losses from Jio, and has slashed FY17-18 consol EPS by 20 per cent.
